1
00:00:05,287 --> 00:00:10,365
Then śrama eva hi kevalam[SB: 1.2.8]
As Prabhupād liked to say,

2
00:00:10,365 --> 00:00:13,225
“Then your life 
is a useless waste of time.”

3
00:00:13,465 --> 00:00:16,805
[Karma | Past Lives]

4
00:00:17,065 --> 00:00:21,375
Then all you’re doing 
is accumulating karma

5
00:00:21,375 --> 00:00:24,258
and suffering or enjoying—
the reactions of karma.

6
00:00:24,258 --> 00:00:26,312
You’re on the Ferris wheel.

7
00:00:26,312 --> 00:00:28,842
By accumulated sukriti
(pious activities)

8
00:00:28,842 --> 00:00:31,842
you’re going to a higher position, 
heavenly planets.

9
00:00:31,842 --> 00:00:37,232
Exhausting all your enjoyment credits, 
gradually descending into lower species,

10
00:00:37,232 --> 00:00:40,273
going up again …
over and over again.

11
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:45,312
ā-brahma-bhuvanāl lokāḥ
punar āvartino ’rjuna

12
00:00:45,312 --> 00:00:48,762
mām upetya tu kaunteya
punar janma na vidyate
[Bg: 8.16]

13
00:00:48,762 --> 00:00:55,452
I forget … (don’t) get the last line.
punar janma na vidyate? No …

14
00:00:55,452 --> 00:01:00,432
Anyway, it’s mentioned in the Gita
by Kṛṣṇa to Arjun, He is saying,

15
00:01:00,432 --> 00:01:08,202
“Even Brahmā on Brahmā-loka …”
And it says in the Bhāgavatam,

16
00:01:08,202 --> 00:01:12,500
ā-viriñcyād amaṅgalam.
Viriñci means Brahmā.

17
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:17,869
Amaṅgalam—there’s a certain amount 
of inauspiciousness in his position.

18
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:21,259
It’s given as an example 
of karma-miśra-bhakti

19
00:01:21,259 --> 00:01:24,820
in the B􏰄ṛhad-bhāgavatām􏰄ṛta 
sequence.

20
00:01:24,827 --> 00:01:28,207
So, sometimes it is even said 
the first birth is as Brahmā,

21
00:01:28,207 --> 00:01:31,657
then descending from there. 
How is that possible?

22
00:01:31,657 --> 00:01:37,723
How is it possible for Indra,
the King of heaven, to become a pig?

23
00:01:37,723 --> 00:01:45,033
When a New Age ramblings …

24
00:01:45,033 --> 00:01:49,013
they always like to talk about,
especially the women.

25
00:01:49,013 --> 00:01:56,334
She—“They said, ‘I was a princess
or a queen in my last life.’”

26
00:01:56,334 --> 00:01:57,670
So everyone can 
[remember] …

27
00:01:57,670 --> 00:02:00,876
That sounds really romantic—
you were once a queen

28
00:02:00,876 --> 00:02:05,616
or a king, or a princess …
But they never tell you,

29
00:02:05,616 --> 00:02:11,026
“You were once in the body
of a stool-eating pig.”

30
00:02:11,026 --> 00:02:16,179
Because that won’t sell the same amount
of books or Tarot cards.

31
00:02:16,179 --> 00:02:20,559
But Indra, how embarrassing 
for the King of heaven

32
00:02:20,559 --> 00:02:29,529
to be … to devolve 
into the body of a pig,

33
00:02:29,529 --> 00:02:37,749
and with all the trappings,
surroundings of pig life

34
00:02:37,749 --> 00:02:40,919
with a pig wife, 
little piglets.

35
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:44,119
And Brahma and the other gods, 
they are very embarrassed

36
00:02:44,119 --> 00:02:48,415
to see one of their own, 
executive officer-jīva

37
00:02:48,415 --> 00:02:56,505
to descend to such
an abominable position.

38
00:02:56,513 --> 00:02:58,763
So they are trying to …

39
00:02:58,763 --> 00:03:01,763
Who—maybe is Nārada,
I forget who,

40
00:03:01,763 --> 00:03:05,105
but trying to bring him 
to his senses, 
 

41
00:03:05,105 --> 00:03:08,105
and he’s very …
he’s guarding his pig wife

42
00:03:08,105 --> 00:03:10,865
and piglets,
and his pig sty.

43
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:13,455
I mean, 
“He worked for this!

44
00:03:13,455 --> 00:03:17,875
[Laughing] 
He built that sty!”

45
00:03:18,914 --> 00:03:25,117
And so one by one 
they start throwing the piglets

46
00:03:25,117 --> 00:03:28,747
into the pond 
and drowning them,

47
00:03:28,747 --> 00:03:33,917
and he and his wife were thinking, 
“What kind of a cruel man is this?!”

48
00:03:33,917 --> 00:03:39,229
And each piglet that dies, they resume 
their position as a devatā in heaven.

49
00:03:39,229 --> 00:03:42,855
And they are all watching 
this on a big screen in heaven.

50
00:03:42,855 --> 00:03:47,745
The equivalent of a big screen,
[Laughing] and Indra …

51
00:03:47,745 --> 00:03:51,879
Finally it’s just him and his wife.
Then they kill his wife,

52
00:03:51,879 --> 00:03:58,600
then finally his pig body
is given up, 
 

53
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:03,507
and then he resumes his position
in heaven Indra.

54
00:04:03,507 --> 00:04:08,776
And he can see the replay 
on the big screen of what happened,

55
00:04:08,776 --> 00:04:09,776
and they’re saying to him,

56
00:04:09,776 --> 00:04:12,586
“Would you like 
to go back to that?”—No!

57
00:04:12,586 --> 00:04:17,456
Now he’s come to his senses, 
his higher self has kicked in,

58
00:04:17,456 --> 00:04:23,071
and he can understand 
how he degraded.

59
00:04:23,731 --> 00:04:29,170
It’s with experience, 
by practical experience we know that—

60
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:34,729
it’s difficult to improve, 
to upgrade,

61
00:04:34,729 --> 00:04:38,989
but you can become degraded
in 15 minutes.

62
00:04:38,989 --> 00:04:45,009
It’s amazing how quickly 
degradation sets in.

63
00:04:45,053 --> 00:04:50,763
As one of the great writers, 
perhaps Hemingway,

64
00:04:51,093 --> 00:04:54,609
in a description 
said of someone,

65
00:04:54,609 --> 00:05:03,549
“At first things started to fall
apart gradually, then all at once.”

66
00:05:03,924 --> 00:05:10,244
So, asat-saṅga-tyāga,—ei vaiṣṇava-ācāra
[Cc: 2.22.87]

67
00:05:10,399 --> 00:05:16,739
One of the first symptoms of the serious 
pursuit of Vaishnavism in earnest

68
00:05:16,739 --> 00:05:23,550
is asat-saṅga-tyāga—to give up
bad association, mundane association.

69
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:27,027
Or those who are addicted …

70
00:05:27,027 --> 00:05:29,987
associating with those
who are addicted to the mundane.

